dataIdInfo.idPurp: Input for the CDSS. Assist Colorado Water Conservation Board and Division of Water Resources in water management and administration.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Spatial and informational database of irrigated parcels in Division 6 for the 2000 growing season in support of the CDSS.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: CDSS funded by Colorado Water Conservation Board (CWCB) and Colorado Division of Water Resources (CDWR). Input to dataset from various water users including water commissioners, ditch companies, water management groups, and individual farmers.

Consts.useLimit: CWCB and CDWR provide no warranty to the users of this information as to the accuracy, reliability or completeness of the data. Information is subject to change according to additional input during subsequent phases of the CDSS project. The user assumes all responsibility for the use of this data.

dataLineage.statement: This dataset is a dirivative of the Division 6 Master Parcel dataset and crop type information provided by SSI in the original Yr 2000 irrigated lands data.

prcStep.stepDesc: The Division 6, Master Parcel dataset was copied and used as a base for the 2000 dataset. The dataset was used in combination with 1990's DOQQs, and 2005 NAIP aerial imagery, and max NDVI Landsat imagery to refine field boundaries and identify additional potentially irrigated fields based on a visual assessment.

Multidate Landsat 7 images were composited and run through the NDVI model to obtain NDVI Max composites, which were then used to determine irrigated vs non-irrigated lands, and also where fields needed to be divided for potentially different crops.

Crop Type Assignment: The original 2000 dataset (circa 2004) was converted into a raster classified by crop type. Zonal attributes were calculated to determine the majority crop in each field of the new dataset.
Crops such as bluegrass (on golf courses) orchards and vinyards - as denoted in the Master parcel dataset - were reviewed individually against ground truth data and aerial photos to ensure those classifications were accurate in 2000. Changes were made accordingly.
Where crop information was not available, crops were assigned either based on available data in 2005 or 2010, or interpreted base on location and regional growing practices.

QA/QC: Irrigated parcels were checked again in a QAQC procedure to ensure they comply with CDSS standards. This included checking all attributes including: Crop Type and Irrigation Type normalization, SW_WDID attributes are not duplicated, all SW_WDID attributes exist in the structure table of HydroBase. Edits and adjustments were made accordingly. All parcels comply with CDSS standards.
